Chucking up the ✌🏾 to 2022 
Enjoyed the good times & prayed for God to guide my steps during difficult ones. This was a year of going inward & reconnecting with myself. Constantly checking in with myself, making shifts & breaking down walls that had been put up as emotional safeguards but no longer served me. Truly working on becoming a better version of myself. 

Few things I’m proud of this year:

Leaning into a deeper level of vulnerability

Showing up for people I care about & allowing them to show up for me. 

Working on a heightened level of grace first towards myself & also to others 

In moments of anxiousness asking myself “what’s the best that can happen” if I felt myself jumping straight to worst case

Felt more of my emotions instead of trying to Intellectualize them. When angered, tried to dig deeper to identify the true underlying emotion

Establishing boundaries for better self care & learning more & more to not feeling guilty about upholding them. 
Communicating these boundaries with family, friends & colleagues when necessary, being vocal if we weren’t in alignment & not feeling guilty about not wavering.

Being honest when I needed & deserved breaks. I work(ed) A LOT, but believe it or not, I took more time to myself outside of work than I’ve ever done…slowly shedding the fear that these “breaks” would disappoint others, that I’d miss something, or cause too much of an inconvenience to what was happening on the work front. It’s never going to be the perfect time & there’s always going to be something…take care of yourself. These moments of disconnecting allowed me to come back better connected & more centered during chaos.

Let people live in their own realities, without feeling the need to always offer my opinion 

I didn’t get it right 100% nor was I my best self at times, definitely a work in progress. But I’m proud of my growth. The work has been hard & intentional

Yes I had some great professional moments this year, but this year was personal. 

Intentionally carrying this glow into 2023 ✨🫶🏾🙏🏾❤️ #2022 #2023 #HappyNewYear

One of my top moments in Bali: I talk to God a lot. In Bali I was able to have the conversations free from the everyday noise and distractions. I asked God for a sign on some things and the next morning I was here witnessing what the locals said was one of the best sunrises they had seen in years. They said sometimes it’s cloudy so you can’t really see the sun clearly. My driver snapped these in the parking lot of a coffee shop on my iPhone, no fancy filter…just God’s beauty in purest form.

It was even more confirmation because I was thinking about putting this sunrise trip off to go to brunch with some people I’d met there. But my intuition said, no go to the sunrise. And I did. One of the most beautiful sights I’ve ever witnessed. I had chills, tears of joy were shed. Truly spiritual. I hear you God. ❤️

Moments like this ❤️🥺🫶🏾
My 6 year old cousin thought he was going to monster jam yesterday and instead got to meet his favorite at the concert. He LOVES Baby and asks me “Where Lil Baby?” everytime I see him 🙄🤣. Yesterday, he FaceTimed me after so excited, still cheesing “Britney, I met Lil Baby. Me and Lil Baby got the same shoes!” 

Working in this business it’s easy to get jaded, but moments like this and seeing the impact these artist have on people’s lives make all the difference. Hearing him say “Lil Baby” in the video with such excitement made my day. Thank you @lilbaby for being so gracious. Love you kidd 😊

⭐️A few moments with family ❤️⭐️

I have a HUGE family so 10 slides couldn’t begin to cover the moments we shared this year, but here’s a small glimpse. 

⭐️Took my mom to see Usher in Vegas
⭐️My dad turned 60
⭐️My sister graduated from UCLA
⭐️My great grandma passed 🕊️
⭐️Birthdays birthdays birthdays 

It’s easy to overlook the beauty in everyday moments. But they are the ones that make life special. This year reinforced that for me. The older I get, the more I’m reminded tragedy can happen anytime. Don't take your loved ones for granted. Show up for your family. Life is so short and we need to make the most of it now because that's all we’re really guaranteed. 🥰❤️

2023 was transformative ✨🥰❤️
I can’t thank God enough 🙏🏾
⭐️ 🇲🇽 Mexico 🇲🇽 ⭐️

In 2023…I smiled and laughed a lot. Here’s a small glimpse. 

My words for 2023 were love, nourish, glow & grace. Picking these words in Dec 2022, I had no way of knowing to what extent these words would shape my 2023. 

Little did I know, God was about to restructure my life at the top of 2023. Closing one chapter allowed me to embark on the most beautiful & personal journey. This year I was blessed to focus on me. I prioritized my happiness & healing. I prioritized love & laughter. I got comfortable putting myself first. I fed my soul & spirit. I did the work. 

Grateful to all those who throughout this year commented on how happy I seemed, how I’m “glowing” (I mean I clearly stayed on a beach so the tan was poppin 🤣), how I seem different/lighter. I received it all. The external reassurance was nice. However the most important thing was I truly felt it within myself. The work done inward radiating outward.🌸🦋💋

I’m so thankful for this departing year. I’m forever changed. I now embrace the new. 
Here’s to 2024…I’m ready 😎😉🥰🙌🏾🙏🏾
#Blessed #Grateful #Love #GodIsGood
Best way to start the new year - celebrating life & love! Let’s go 2024 ❤️☺️
